    "# AQA A-Level Computer Science — SQL Notebook 1\n",
    "## The Library Database: SELECT, WHERE, ORDER BY\n",
    "\n",
    "**Topics covered:** `SELECT`, `FROM`, `WHERE`, `ORDER BY`, `INSERT`, `UPDATE`, `DELETE`\n",
    "\n",
    "**AQA Syllabus reference:** Section 4.10.4 — Structured Query Language (SQL)\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### The scenario\n",
    "\n",
    "You are working with a library database system. The database has three tables:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Table | What it stores |\n",
    "|-------|---------------|\n",
    "| `Member` | People who are registered with the library |\n",
    "| `Book` | Books held in the library's collection |\n",
    "| `Loan` | A record of which member borrowed which book, and when |\n",
    "\n",
    "Run the setup cell below first, then work through each section in order.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bf44cccd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## ⚙️ Setup — Run this cell first"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "8d404df8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%load_ext sql\n",
    "%sql sqlite:///databases/library.db\n",
    "%config SqlMagic.displaycon = False\n",
    "print(\"✓ Connected to library.db\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1ad5d0a8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## The Database Schema\n",
    "\n",
    "Before writing any queries, study the structure of the three tables.\n",
    "Understanding the fields and relationships is essential in the exam.\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Member                      Loan                        Book\n",
    "──────────────────          ────────────────────        ──────────────────────\n",
    "MemberID  (PK)  ◄───────── MemberID  (FK)              BookID    (PK) ◄──────\n",
    "FirstName                   LoanID    (PK)    ──────── BookID    (FK)\n",
    "LastName                    BookID    (FK)              Title\n",
    "Email                       LoanDate                    Author\n",
    "JoinDate                    ReturnDate *                Genre\n",
    "Active                                                   YearPublished\n",
    "                                                         Available\n",
    "```\n",
    "`*` ReturnDate is NULL if the book has not yet been returned.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Primary Key (PK):** uniquely identifies each row in a table.\n",
    "**Foreign Key (FK):** links to the primary key of another table.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
