    "---\n",
    "## Part 3 — Filtering with WHERE\n",
    "\n",
    "`WHERE` lets you filter rows to only those matching a condition.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3a. Worked example — filtering by genre\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "d9edb38b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%%sql\n",
    "SELECT Title, Author\n",
    "FROM Book\n",
    "WHERE Genre = 'Dystopian';"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7e062f8c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3b. Practice — filtering by a number\n",
    "\n",
    "Write a query to show the `Title` and `YearPublished` of all books published before 1950.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "8887ee72",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
