    "---\n",
    "## Part 6 — Modifying Data with UPDATE\n",
    "\n",
    "`UPDATE` changes existing rows. **Always use a `WHERE` clause**\n",
    "or you will update every row in the table.\n",
    "\n",
    "```sql\n",
    "UPDATE TableName\n",
    "SET Column1 = Value1\n",
    "WHERE condition;\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### 6a. Worked example — marking a book as returned\n",
    "\n",
    "Loan 1 has been returned. Update the `ReturnDate`.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "83c8ccf9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%%sql\n",
    "UPDATE Loan\n",
    "SET ReturnDate = '2024-06-15'\n",
    "WHERE LoanID = 6;"
   ]
  },
